es?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095112&amp;id=fig06f">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig07" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.302095112/asset/images/095112fig07.jpeg" height="716" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig07" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 7</span> Diagram shows the formation of a <span data-style="small-caps">D</span>-loop (left) and an <span data-style="small-caps">L</span>-loop (right) from the embryonic cardiac tube (center). <i>A</i> = atria, <i>Ao</i> = aorta, <i>BC</i> = bulbus cordis, <i>LV</i> = left ventricle, <i>PA</i> = pulmonary artery, <i>RV</i> = right ventricle, <i>TA</i> = truncus arteriosus, <i>V</i> = embryonic left ventricle. (Reprinted, with permission, from reference <a href="#r7" role="doc-biblioref" data-xml-rid="r7">7</a>.)<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095112&amp;id=fig07">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.302095112/asset/images/095112fig08a.jpeg" height="1397" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095112&amp;id=fig08a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.302095112/asset/images/095112fig08b.jpeg" height="1460" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095112&amp;id=fig08b">Download as PowerPoint</a